#Text=The host Utah Jazz blew out the visiting Chicago Bulls , 110 - 80 , on Wednesday evening at Vivint Smart Home Arena .
#Text=Utah ( 8 - 11 ) needed a win badly , and earned one in emphatic style on Wednesday .
#Text=The Jazz had dropped eight of their previous ten games , and have been struggling to adjust to the absence of star center Rudy Gobert , who is sidelined with a knee injury .
#Text=However , the team showed no signs of struggle on Wednesday , as the team earned a 30 - point blowout win on the backs of six double - digit scoring performances .
#Text=Utah 's bench performed exceptionally well in the win , accounting for 51 points .
#Text=Sixth man Rodney Hood led the bench unit with 19 points , including three three - pointers .
#Text=For the starters , big man Derrick Favors led the team with 23 points on impressive 8 - of - 11 shooting .
#Text=Favors added seven rebounds , a block , and a steal .
#Text=Chicago ( 3 - 13 ) owns the worst record in the Eastern Conference and has won only one of its ten road games to this point .
#Text=While the Bulls have many promising young players , Friday 's blowout loss far from exemplified that .
#Text=Rookie lottery pick Lauri Markkanen had a season low of just three points while shooting 1 - of - 9 on the night .
#Text=Point guard Kris Dunn , meanwhile , had four turnovers while dishing out only one assist .
#Text=As a whole .
#Text=Chicago shot an abysmal 37 percent overall from the field .
#Text=The poor shooting was compounded by ice - cold perimeter play , as the team hit only five three - pointers on the night .
#Text=On Friday , the Bulls will visit Golden State , while Utah will host the Milwaukee Bucks on Saturday .
